 1----Instance Variable (Object Variable)

An instance variable is a variable that belongs to an object. It is declared inside a class but outside any method.

Example
class Student {
    String name;   // Instance variable
    int age;       // Instance variable
}

Here,

name is an instance variable.
age is an instance variable.

When an object is created, every object gets its own copy of these variables.

2---- Reference Variable

A reference variable stores the address (reference) of an object.

It does not store the object itself.


3----Quick Difference
Instance Variable   	Reference Variable
Stores object's data  	Stores object's address
Declared inside class	  Declared when creating an object
Each object has its own copy   	Points to an object
Example: name, age   	Example: s1, student


4----Student s1(compile time) = new Student();(Runtime )
Student → Class
s1 → Reference variable
new Student() → Creates the object
name, age (inside the class) → Instance variables



-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1---------Why are they different?
C++
Student s1;
The object is created directly.
s1 is the object.
Memory is usually allocated on the stack (unless you use new).



Java
Student s1 = new Student();
The object is always created using new.
s1 is not the object.
s1 only stores a reference (address) to the object.

NOTE==Student student1;
This line does NOT create an object. 
It only creates a reference variable.

--Creating an object
Now write
student1 = new Student();

This is where the magic happens.
The keyword new

*allocates memory dynamically
*creates the object
*initializes default values
*returns the address of that object

2---Comparison
C++	          Java
Student s1;    	Student s1 = new Student();
s1 is the object    	s1 is a reference variable
Object can be on the stack  	Object is created on the heap
new is optional   	new is required for normal object creation
